# Timed Multiplication Display

## Overview
Displays the square of a number for an initial duration, followed by its multiplication table at regular intervals.

## Board
Arty A7 (Artix-7)

## Tools
- Verilog
- Xilinx Vivado

## Description
The design takes an input number from DIP switches. 

- For the first 5 seconds, it displays the square of the number.
- After that, it sequentially displays the multiplication table of the number, updating every second.

## Inputs
- DIP switches (input number)
- Clock
- Reset

## Outputs
- LEDs (display output)

## Notes
This design combines timing control, sequential logic, and arithmetic operations, and can be modeled using an FSM.
